# Project Rules

Before creating or modifying UI components, ALWAYS reference design-system.md.

Use ONLY CSS variables defined in globals.css. No hardcoded values.

When using Tailwind:

- Use arbitrary values to reference CSS vars: `bg-[var(--color-primary)]`
- Or use custom component classes defined in globals.css
- NEVER use arbitrary Tailwind values (no p-7, no text-gray-650)
- NEVER hardcode colors (no #3b82f6, no rgb values)

Dark mode is handled automatically via CSS variables in globals.css - do not add manual dark: variants.

When creating reusable component patterns, add them to globals.css using @apply in the @layer components section.

## Layout & Responsiveness

- ALL components must be fully mobile responsive

## Global Components

- Navbar/Header and Footer components belong ONLY in root layout.
  tsx
- Page routes contain page-specific content

## Typography

- Primary Font: `var(--font-primary)` - Use for all text
- Secondary Font: `var(--font-secondary)` - Only use when explicitly instructed (e.g., code blocks)
- Body text uses primary font by default
- Fonts are defined in layout.tsx and can be changed there without modifying CSS

## Background Elevation

- `var(--background)` - Page/section backgrounds
- `var(--background-elevated)` - Cards, containers, sections
- `var(--background-elevated-high)` - ONLY for floating overlays (modals, dropdowns, tooltips) - use sparingly

## Content Management

ALL text content must be separated from components and stored in src/data/.

Structure:

- Global content (nav, footer): `src/data/navigation.ts`, `src/data/footer.ts`
- Page content: `src/data/pages/[pagename].ts` where the object structure mirrors the page structure

Example:

```ts
// src/data/pages/home.ts
export const homeContent = {
  hero: { title: "...", subtitle: "..." },
  cta: { heading: "...", button: "..." },
  features: { heading: "...", items: [...] },
}
```

- NEVER hardcode text strings in components
- Import data files directly in components - no prop passing for content
- Avoid unnecessary interface typing for content props
- If no specific content is provided, use clear placeholder text in data objects (e.g., "Hero Title", "Feature description goes here")
- Use clear, semantic key names that match the component/section purpose (hero, features, testimonials)
- Use camelCase for all keys
- Avoid generic names (section1, content, data)

## Interaction & Animation

- Simple UI toggles may use native HTML semantics (e.g. <details>) where appropriate
- If an interaction requires custom enter/exit animations, height/layout animations, coordinated open/close behavior, or future extensibility beyond basic toggling, THEN prefer React-managed state using hooks (useState, useEffect)
- In such cases:
  - Mark components as "use client"
  - Use React state to control interaction
  - For animations, follow this priority:
    1. Tailwind transition utilities (transition-colors, transition-opacity, etc.) for simple state changes
    2. Framer Motion library for all other animations (enter/exit, layout, gestures, complex sequences)
    3. Raw CSS only as last resort or when Motion has API limitations

Do not refactor, restructure, or modify any code that I have personally added or changed unless I explicitly instruct you to do so.
